{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Regulate lifeguard provision and require them to use coloured flags",
        "additional_details": "I want all beaches to have coloured flags that indicate where it is safe to swim and do water sports.\r\n\r\nI think it is paramount to make our beaches as safe as possible. I feel that in places like California and Spain, lifeguards are very common. So, why can\u2019t they be common here as well. I also feel that all beaches should have coloured safety flags to indicate where it is safe to swim and do water sports. I think these flags are easy to understand. I note that many beaches already have lifeguards and flags from the RNLI and other organisations. I ask for this to be rolled out to all beaches.",
        "background": "I would like to the Government to regulate lifeguard provision at all major beaches. This would be done at beach towns with 25,000+ residents. I think it is paramount to make our beaches as safe as possible. ",
